  "important_notes": [
    "Planet.init() wires tech tree: calls TechTree.roots.find(), then techTree.addDatabaseTab()/addPlanet(). Also calls generator.generateSector() for every sector and updateBaseCoverage().",
    "Sector.unlocked() depends on hasBase() OR preset.alwaysUnlocked — controls whether player can land.",
    "Sector.threat is computed by Planet.updateBaseCoverage() based on adjacent enemy bases and preset.difficulty.",
    "SectorPreset.initialize() auto-remaps sector index via PlanetData.presets map (vanilla migration support).",
    "PlanetDialog.show() has three modes: 'look' (browse campaign), 'select' (pick sector programmatically), 'planetLaunch' (interplanetary launch from existing base).",
    "Launch flow: PlanetDialog.selectSector() → builds launch button → control.playSector(from, sector) — saves state first, then fires launch animation via core.launchDuration().",
    "CampaignRules are saved/loaded per-planet to Core.settings as JSON (key: '<planetName>-campaign-rules').",
    "CampaignStats are saved/loaded per-planet to Core.settings as JSON (key: '<planetName>-campaign-stats'); statParent allows two planets to share stats.",
    "PlanetGrid is a geodesic sphere of Ptile tiles; sectors.size == grid.tiles.length — direct index mapping.",
    "Planet.statParent allows a child planet to share CampaignStats with its parent (used for shared campaigns)."
  ]
}
